2.1	Introduction
This feature provides statistics for GSM teleservices with SMS, FAX, CS data characteristics over the Circuit Switched Data calls.

There was a limitation in the legacy BSC package. From the existing counter framework it is not possible to detect the HIGH CALL SETUP TIME issue that occurs when the MT UE receives a paging message from the MSC late. HIGH CALL SETUP TIME issues often cause complaints from OPERATOR due to a significant decrease in user expierence quality. To mitigate this issue, in SVR26A a new counter needs to be developed that can calculate time from BSSAP ASSIGNMENT COMPLETE to ALERTING reception so that HIGH CALL SETUP TIME can be detected early and the occurrence frequency and occurrence CELL can be analyzed.


